verses.text_plain: Unto thee, O God, do we give thanks, unto thee do we give thanks: for that thy name is near thy wondrous works declare.
verses.verse_html:
1Unto thee, O God, do we give thanks, unto thee do we give thanks: for that thy name is near thy wondrous works declare. ▼
▼ Al–taschith: or, Destroy not
 , ▼
▼ of: or, for

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Al–taschith: or, Destroy not

verses.text_plain: When I shall receive the congregation I will judge uprightly.
verses.verse_html:
2When I shall receive the congregation I will judge uprightly. ▼
▼ receive…: or, take a set time

footnotes.body_text: ▼ receive…: or, take a set time
footnotes.body_html: ▼ receive…: or, take a set time

verses.text_plain: The earth and all the inhabitants thereof are dissolved: I bear up the pillars of it. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 3The earth and all the inhabitants thereof are dissolved: I bear up the pillars of it. Selah.

verses.text_plain: I said unto the fools, Deal not foolishly: and to the wicked, Lift not up the horn:
verses.verse_html: 4I said unto the fools, Deal not foolishly: and to the wicked, Lift not up the horn:

verses.text_plain: Lift not up your horn on high: speak not with a stiff neck.
verses.verse_html: 5Lift not up your horn on high: speak not with a stiff neck.

verses.text_plain: For promotion cometh neither from the east, nor from the west, nor from the south.
verses.verse_html:
6For promotion cometh neither from the east, nor from the west, nor from the south. ▼
▼ south: Heb. desert

verses.text_plain: But God is the judge: he putteth down one, and setteth up another.
verses.verse_html: 7But God is the judge: he putteth down one, and setteth up another.

verses.text_plain: For in the hand of the Lord there is a cup, and the wine is red; it is full of mixture; and he poureth out of the same: but the dregs thereof, all the wicked of the earth shall wring them out, and drink them.
verses.verse_html: 8For in the hand of the Lord there is a cup, and the wine is red; it is full of mixture; and he poureth out of the same: but the dregs thereof, all the wicked of the earth shall wring them out, and drink them.

verses.text_plain: But I will declare for ever; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.
verses.verse_html: 9But I will declare for ever; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.

verses.text_plain: All the horns of the wicked also will I cut off; but the horns of the righteous shall be exalted.
verses.verse_html: 10All the horns of the wicked also will I cut off; but the horns of the righteous shall be exalted.
